[assistant] Fixed the failing JavaAdapter test setup.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - The manually created `NativeObject` implementation had no Rhino parent/prototype, so `JavaAdapter.createAdapterWrapper()` could not find the top-level scope and `ClassCache`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made:
[assistant] - Updated `JavaAdapterTest.java` to initialize the manually constructed Rhino objects/functions with the proper scope:
[assistant]   - `ScriptRuntime.setObjectProtoAndParent(implementation, scope)`
[assistant]   - `ScriptRuntime.setFunctionProtoAndParent(..., context, scope)`
[assistant] 
[assistant] File changed:
[assistant] - `tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/JavaAdapterTest.java`
[assistant] 
