[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - The test used `java.util.ArrayList` as the JavaAdapter superclass.
[assistant] - HtmlUnit/Rhino reflects fields on the adapter superclass hierarchy.
[assistant] - On JDK 21, reflecting `java.util.AbstractList.modCount` fails because `java.base/java.util` is not opened.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fix:
[assistant] - Replaced `ArrayList`/`List` adapter targets with test-owned public API types:
[assistant]   - `AdapterBase`
[assistant]   - `AdapterMarker`
[assistant] - Constructed the adapter through the public Rhino `JavaAdapter` function using `NativeJavaClass`, rather than using JavaScript `Packages.java.util.*`.
[assistant] - This keeps the test on supported behavior while avoiding illegal reflective access into JDK internals.
[assistant] 
