dapter superclass hierarchy.\n- On JDK 21, reflecting `java.util.AbstractList.modCount` fails because `java.base/java.util` is not opened.\n\nFix:\n- Replaced `ArrayList`/`List` adapter targets with test-owned public API types:\n  - `AdapterBase`\n  - `AdapterMarker`\n- Constructed the adapter through the public Rhino `JavaAdapter` function using `NativeJavaClass`, rather than using JavaScript `Packages.java.util.*`.\n- This keeps the test on supported behavior while avoiding illegal reflective access into JDK internals.\n\nUpdated file:\n- `tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/JavaAdapterTest.java`\n\nPer instruction, I did not run the Gradle test locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0583090586bb498c016a2888db98948196b90ee489518d4380\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 591, "output": 740, "cacheRead": 55808, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57139, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781041352626, "responseId": "resp_0583090586bb498c016a2888c97c108196beba25663e8c66d9"}}
